'''ALICEWEB''' is an [[acronym]] for '''A'''ná'''l'''ise de '''I'''nformações de '''C'''omércio '''E'''xterior-'''Web''', the official website of the [[Government of Brazil|Brazilian government]] about their [[foreign trade]] statistics. It was made available from 2001 onwards, aiming at easy and clear publication of [[foreign trade]] statistics. Access to Aliceweb is free. Users can check the data and choose to generate files containing the results of the queries and have these results emailed to them. The system has [[Brazil]]ian foreign trade data from 1989 until the most recent month.
It is developed and maintained by the Secretariat of Foreign Trade (SECEX), of the Ministry of Development, Industry and Foreign Trade (MDIC).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.th/books?id=9w7GBQAAQBAJ&pg=PT207&lpg=PT207&dq=AliceWeb+brazil&source=bl&ots=ZbacFmyLs-&sig=lxRRtceWytwpgyekU3GZT6PlYvY&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj2woyG9azJAhXQCo4KHd22DsYQ6AEIPDAI#v=onepage&q=AliceWeb%20brazil&f=false |title=The Political Economy of Integration: The Experience of Mercosur |author=Jeffrey W. Cason |website=Books.google.co.th |date= |accessdate=2016-02-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.desenvolvimento.gov.br/sitio/interna/interna.php?area=5&menu=607 |title=Comércio Exterior » ALICEWeb, ALICEWeb-Mercosul e Radar Comercial - Ministério do Desenvolvimento, Indústria e Comércio Exterior |language=pt |website=Desenvolvimento.gov.br |date= |accessdate=2016-02-21}}</ref>
